If you're taking CS 70 right now, I'm not sure but I am assuming you might not have the right background to take CS 189 - an advanced upperdivision course with de-facto prerequisites of Math 53, EE 16AB, EECS 126/127.

-----------------------

Taking 170&189 and some other classes right now. It's doable but you'd better have a strong background in at least 53&54/EE16AB. Expect a lot of work as well.

----------------------- To the student who is deleting other peoples responses: stop. 

I am currently taking both, without having taken 126 or 127. It is certainly doable, just be advised an enormous amount of time goes into homework, and even outside of that, more time must be spent to learn the material. Personally, 70 and 170 had comparable workloads, but 189 is significantly more time than any lower div I took.
